body_html:
Okay, the Sanity Checks seemed to fail because the filegroups wasnt ordered alphabetically (I think). I have now updated the filegroups so the "//tensorflow/contrib/seq2seq:all_files" is alphabetically correctly placed in the tensorflow/BUILD's filegroup.

This was the FAILED stack trace from the Sanity Checks:

=== Sanity check step 3 of 4: do_buildifier (buildifier check) ===

Running do_buildifier on 112 files

tensorflow/BUILD # listsort unsafesort sort:filegroup.data

buildifier took 1 s

FAIL: buildifier found errors and/or warnings in above BUILD files.
buildifier suggested the following changes:
123a124
>         "//tensorflow/contrib/seq2seq:all_files",
126d126
<         "//tensorflow/contrib/seq2seq:all_files",
Please fix manually or run buildifier <file> to auto-fix.

body:
Okay, the `Sanity Checks` seemed to fail because the filegroups wasnt ordered alphabetically (I think). I have now updated the filegroups so the `"//tensorflow/contrib/seq2seq:all_files"` is alphabetically correctly placed in the `tensorflow/BUILD`'s filegroup.

This was the `FAILED` stack trace from the `Sanity Checks`:

```
=== Sanity check step 3 of 4: do_buildifier (buildifier check) ===

Running do_buildifier on 112 files

tensorflow/BUILD # listsort unsafesort sort:filegroup.data

buildifier took 1 s

FAIL: buildifier found errors and/or warnings in above BUILD files.
buildifier suggested the following changes:
123a124
>         "//tensorflow/contrib/seq2seq:all_files",
126d126
<         "//tensorflow/contrib/seq2seq:all_files",
Please fix manually or run buildifier <file> to auto-fix.
```
